./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0074_1777762507.log:26208:+- Added depth-2 garden watcher end-to-end test coverage (frac-0074): `tests/test_garden_watcher.py` now includes `GardenWatcherEndToEndTests`, which drives the public garden watcher path through deterministic brightness/time snapshot building, JSON-safe operator summary generation, and atomic runtime-state persistence. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/garden_watcher.py` now exposes `build_garden_state`, `summarize_garden_state`, and `write_current_garden_state`, while `update_garden_state` delegates through the deterministic builder so existing callers keep the same one-path behavior. `tests/test_test_garden_watcher_depth.py` pins the garden watcher test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Startup identity anchors remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0074_1777762507.log:26210: - Added depth-2 gallery-x11-runtime end-to-end test coverage (frac-0073): `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` now includes coverage for `load_playlist`, `render_art`, `render_overlay`, and `init_pygame_display` using mocked data and a dummy SDL driver. A scoping bug in `my-claw/tools/gallery/gallery_x11.py` where overlay rendering logic was inadvertently placed inside `init_pygame_display` was fixed. A depth gate ensures `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` is pinned at fractal depth >= 2. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0074_1777762507.log:26212: - Added depth-2 functional-harmony end-to-end test coverage (frac-0072): `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` now includes `FunctionalHarmonyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing harmony public API through live-like keyboard/garden/outdoor/inner inputs, resolved harmonic planning, reharm lookup, modulation continuity checks, score-tree section construction, and JSON-safe round-trip output. The end-to-end scenarios verify meaningful `HarmonicPlan` fields (`G:lydian` keyboard authority, extended palette, pedal-point voicing, scene keys, section functions/cadences/progressions, chord-degree triads, harmonic functions, transition intents, and modulation path), align `reharm_plan_for_song()` / `progression_bank_for_section()` with the resolved plan, assert tension and cadence targets across the arc, and prove `ScoreTree` persistence preserves derived harmonic function and transition intent metadata. `tests/test_test_functional_harmony_depth.py` pins `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function harmony assertions and production `reharmonizer.py`, `harmonic_planner.py`, and `score_tree.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4487 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
