./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0074_1777762507.log:34251:+- **Details:** Red phase was confirmed before implementation: `pytest tests/test_garden_watcher.py::GardenWatcherEndToEndTests -q` failed with `ImportError: cannot import name 'build_garden_state' from 'garden_watcher'`. The depth gate initially surfaced console `pytest` importing the SDP CLI classifier before the repo-local mock, so `tests/test_test_garden_watcher_depth.py` now uses the deterministic local `importlib.util` pattern already used by nearby depth gates. After implementation, `pytest tests/test_garden_watcher.py tests/test_test_garden_watcher_depth.py -q` passed with `48 passed`, and the startup identity anchor command `pytest tests/test_cli_identity_hardening.py tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring tests/test_narrative_api_main.py::test_asgi_module_startup_bootstraps_identity_persistence_between_imports -q` passed with `9 passed`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0074_1777762507.log:34263:+- Added depth-2 garden watcher end-to-end test coverage (frac-0074): `tests/test_garden_watcher.py` now includes `GardenWatcherEndToEndTests`, which drives the public garden watcher path through deterministic brightness/time snapshot building, JSON-safe operator summary generation, and atomic runtime-state persistence. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/garden_watcher.py` now exposes `build_garden_state`, `summarize_garden_state`, and `write_current_garden_state`, while `update_garden_state` delegates through the deterministic builder so existing callers keep the same one-path behavior. `tests/test_test_garden_watcher_depth.py` pins the garden watcher test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4498 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0074_1777762507.log:34265: - Added depth-2 gallery-x11-runtime end-to-end test coverage (frac-0073): `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` now includes coverage for `load_playlist`, `render_art`, `render_overlay`, and `init_pygame_display` using mocked data and a dummy SDL driver. A scoping bug in `my-claw/tools/gallery/gallery_x11.py` where overlay rendering logic was inadvertently placed inside `init_pygame_display` was fixed. A depth gate ensures `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` is pinned at fractal depth >= 2. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
