./sdp/verification/t-018@20260416t181925zc-verify.md:27:The code follows the established patterns in the `senseweave/render` package. The use of frozen dataclasses for `ExportResult` and the naming conventions for sidecar files are consistent with the rest of the project. The integration into the `poll_loop` startup sequence in `daemon.py` also aligns with recent hardening requirements.
./sdp/verification/t-018@20260416t181925zc-verify.md:30:No security vulnerabilities were identified. Metadata serialization uses standard JSON and XML libraries. File operations use safe patterns (temporary files with `os.replace` for sidecars). The hardening of the `bootstrap_identity` sequence ensures that the instance identity is minted and persisted before any external announcement occurs, preventing unauthenticated or anonymous federation broadcasts.
./sdp/verification/t-018@20260416t181925zc-verify.md:36:- [x] Hardening gap in `daemon.py` — severity: minor (fixed). `bootstrap_identity()` was called after the `startup_banner` in `daemon.py`, unlike in `cypherclaw_daemon.py`. This was corrected by moving the identity bootstrap to the earliest possible point in the startup flow.
./sdp/verification/t-018@20260416t181925zc-verify.md:42:The core provenance integration is solid and correctly implements the spec. The minor startup ordering inconsistency in `daemon.py` has been addressed to satisfy the mandatory hardening checks. The project is now ready for the next phase of deployment.
