n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: [x] **Issue — severity: blocking**: New self-critique logic is not wired into the active composition pipeline. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py` and `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py` continue to call `score_from_mood(...)` directly in piece generation; `revise_score(...)` from `senseweave.self_critique` is never imported or used by composition/playback flow..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Integrate the new `revise_score(...)` path into score generation before tracker/build or playback handoff (both gate-backed and fallback paths)..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that verifies a piece goes through critique/revision before being finalized for playback, with assertions that failed metrics can trigger one bounded rewrite attempt and that the final score is selected from the two-pass result..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Incomplete budget enforcement: budget fields for grain density, global density multiplier, LLM suppression, and DSP budget are computed but never applied in `tracker_solo_song`, so sample/grain and primary-form fallback is not actually enforced (`my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py`, `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`). Severity: blocking..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Startup hardening gap: `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()` before startup announcement and main loop, while this path is still part of the runnable daemon entry points (`my-claw/docs/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` and system scripts/tests reference it), so first-boot identity creation is not guaranteed in that mode. Severity: blocking..\n"}
