sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0074_1777762507.log:12313:- Added depth-2 federation-discovery end-to-end test coverage (frac-0071): `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` now ships a `FederationDiscoveryEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public `discover_peers`, `save_peer_registry`, `load_peer_registry`, and `merge_peer_registry` surface end-to-end through fakes for `tailscale status --json` and the `/federation/v1/identity` endpoint. The end-to-end scenarios cover the full discover → save → load → re-scan → merge → save cycle (verifying meaningful `PeerInfo` fields, JSON-safe registry payloads, `to_dict`/`from_dict` round-trips, online/offline flag flips for vanished peers, `first_seen` preservation for returning peers, and online-on-arrival semantics for new peers), multi-IP peer fall-through where a later IP responds after an earlier IP refuses, and an empty rescan that marks every previously seen peer offline while preserving its identity and timestamps. `tests/test_test_federation_discovery_depth.py` pins `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class, loading `sdp.fractal.classify_depth` via `importlib.util` to remain deterministic against the local classifier. Existing function-level federation discovery assertions and the production `promptclaw/federation/discovery.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4483 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
